{{Infobox basketball league | title = 2. deild karla | current_season = | logo = | pixels = | caption = | sport = [[Basketball]] | founded = 1973 | folded = | inaugural = 1973 | ceo = [[Hannes S. Jónsson]] | fame = | motto = | levels = 3 | pyramid = Icelandic basketball league system | promotion = [[1. deild karla (basketball)|Division I]] | relegation = [[3. deild karla (basketball)|Division III]] | domest_cup = [[Icelandic Men's Basketball Cup|Bikarkeppni KKÍ]] | supercup = [[Icelandic Men's Basketball Supercup|Meistarakeppni karla]] | teams = 10 | country = {{ISL}} | confed = [[FIBA Europe]] | champions = [[Ungmennafélagið Sindri]] | most_champs = [[Laugdælir]] (4 titles) | singles = | TV = | website = [http://www.kki.is/ KKÍ.is] }}
'''2. deild karla''' ({{lang-en|Men's 2. Division}}) or '''D2''' is the third tier [[basketball]] competition among clubs in [[Iceland]]. It is organized by the [[Icelandic Basketball Federation]] ({{lang-is|Körfuknattleikssamband Íslands – KKÍ}}). It consists of 10 teams and the season consists of a home-and-away schedule of 18 games. The top four [[reserve team|non-reserve teams]] meet in a playoff for the victory in the league and [[Promotion and relegation|promotion]] to [[1. deild karla (basketball)|1. deild karla]] ({{lang-is|1. deild karla}}).<ref>[http://kki.is/log-og-reglugerdir/reglugerdir/yfirlit-reglugerda/reglugerd-um-korfuknattleiksmot/ Reglugerð umkörfuknattleiksmót]</ref>
==History==
===Creation===
2. deild karla originated in 1973 and, as of the 2017-2018 season, consists of 10 teams.<ref>[http://kki.is/motamal/leikir-og-urslit/motayfirlit/Deildir-flokkar?league_id=232 2. deild karla (2018)]</ref> [[Laugdælir]] have won the most championships with 4.<ref>[http://gamli.kki.is/meistaratitlar.asp?adgerd=FlkIsl&keppni=2.%20deild%20karla 2. deild karla]</ref>
