{{Unreferenced|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}
A '''creance''' is a long light cord used to tether a flying [[hawk]] or [[falcon]] during training in [[falconry]]. They are used both when the bird is young, and when the bird has been taken out of the aviary for a moult or other reasons.

The creance itself is thin, designed to be of as little inconvenience to the bird as possible. It's threaded through the [[swivel]] and tied with a [[falconer's knot]]. The creance typically extends to around 25 metres (82&nbsp;feet), at which point the bird should be ready to fly free (without the use of the creance).

==See also==
*[[Leash]]
*[[Lead (tack)]]
*[[Fiador (tack)]]

