{{Infobox rugby team | teamname = Duendes | image = Duendes Rugby Club Crest.svg | imagesize = 120px | location = [[Rosario]], [[Argentina]] | countryflag = Argentina | fullname = Duendes Rugby Club | union = [[Unión de Rugby de Rosario|URR]] | nickname = ''Verdinegro'' | shortname = Duendes | founded = {{Start date and years ago|df=yes|1957|1|5}} | ground = Las Delicias | url = https://www.duendes.com.ar/ | president = Camilo Boffelli | coach = | league = Torneo Apertura | season = 2018 | position = 2° |pattern_la1=|pattern_b1=_blackquarters23|pattern_ra1=|leftarm1=000000|body1=339900|rightarm1=339900|shorts1=000000|pattern_so1=_hoops_black|socks1=339900 |pattern_la2= |pattern_b2=|pattern_ra2= |leftarm2=|body2=|rightarm2=|shorts2=|pattern_so2=|socks2= }}
'''Duendes Rugby Club''' is an [[Argentina|Argentine]] [[rugby union]] and [[field hockey]] club sited in [[Rosario, Santa Fe]]. The rugby team currently plays at [[Torneo del Litoral]], the first division of the [[Unión de Rugby de Rosario]] (URR) league system.
==History== Duendes Rugby Club was founded in 1957 and registered with the Rosario Union that same year. After just one season the club won the promotion to the top division of the URR league system and won its first title in 1960.
Along with [[Club Atlético del Rosario|Atlético del Rosario]] and [[Jockey Club de Rosario|Jockey Club]], Duendes is one of the most successful clubs in its city of origin, having won the [[Unión de Rugby de Rosario]] championship 15 times. The club also won the [[Torneo del Litoral]] tournament 12 times.<ref>[https://urr.org.ar/duendes-campeon-del-litoral/ Duendes, campeón del Litoral], URR, 14 Oct 2018</ref>
At national level, Duendes is also the most winning team from Rosario, having won the [[Nacional de Clubes]] title twice, in 2004 and 2009.<ref name="history">{{cite news |url=http://www.duendes.com.ar/historia.php |title=Duendes History |language=Spanish |date=21 May 2010 |accessdate=22 May 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100312095152/http://www.duendes.com.ar/historia.php |archivedate=12 March 2010 |df= }}</ref> On four occasions (1968, 1969, 1972 and 1993) the team remained unbeaten all season.
In 2009 Duendes won the inaugural [[Torneo del Interior]], the national competition for clubs not from Buenos Aires. As winners of this tournament, the team qualified directly to the semi-finals of the overhauled Nacional de Clubes.
In November, 2011, Duendes won its first [[Nacional de Clubes]] championship, defeating [[Club La Tablada|La Tablada]] 26-23 in the final match. The MVP was the [[fly-half]] Mateo Escalante, the game's top scorer with 16 points converted with a 100% accuracy.<ref>[http://www.rugbyfun.com.ar/nota.asp?not_codigo=75113 "La revancha de Duendes"] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120520111032/http://www.rugbyfun.com.ar/nota.asp?not_codigo=75113 |date=May 20, 2012 }}, Rugbyfun website, 2011-11-26</ref>
==Titles== *'''[[Nacional de Clubes]] (3)''': 2004, 2009, 2011 *'''[[Torneo del Interior]] (2)''': 2003, 2009 *'''[[Torneo del Litoral]] (12)''': 2000, 2002, 2006, 2007, 2010, 2011, 2012, 2013, 2014, 2015, 2016, 2018 *'''[[Unión de Rugby de Rosario]] (15)''': 1960, 1962, 1963, 1964, 1965, 1966, 1967, 1968, 1969, 1971, 1972, 1993, 1995, 1996, 1997
