The '''Asian Games mascots''' are [[Character (arts)|fictional characters]], usually an animal native to the area or human figures, who represent the cultural heritage of the place where the [[Asian Games]] are taking place. The mascots are often used to help market the Asian Games to a younger audience. Every [[Asian Games]] since [[1982 Asian Games|1982]] has its own [[mascot]]. Appu, the mascot for the 1982 Asian Games, was the first mascot.
