{{Infobox film | name = The Hockey Players | image = Хоккеисты film poster.jpg | alt = | caption = Russian film poster | film name = {{unbulleted list||[[Russian language|Russian]]: ''Хоккеисты''|(''Khokkeisty'')}} | director = [[Rafail Goldin]] | producer = | writer = [[Yury Trifonov]] | screenplay = | story = | based on = | starring = {{unbulleted list|[[Vyacheslav Shalevich]]|[[Vladimir Ivashov]]|[[Aleksandr Kuznetsov (actor)|Aleksandr Kuznetsov]]|[[Aleksandr Orlov (actor)|Aleksandr Orlov]]|[[Nikolai Rybnikov]]||[[Gennadi Yukhtin]]|[[Georgiy Zhzhonov]]|[[Mikhail Gluzsky]]|[[Lyusyena Ovchinnikova]]|[[Lev Durov]]|[[Viktor Pavlov]]|[[Jacob Lenz]]|[[Kir Bulychev]]<ref name="cite 1"/>}} | narrator = <!-- or: |narrators = --> | music = Leonid Afanasyev | cinematography = [[Timofey Lebeshev]] | editing = Raisa Novikova | studio = [[Mosfilm]] | distributor = Mosfilm | released = {{film date|1965}} ([[Soviet Union]])<!-- {{film date|year|month|day|location}} --> | runtime = 100 minutes | country = Soviet Union | language = Russian | budget = | gross = }}
'''''The Hockey Players''''' ({{lang-ru|Khokkeisty|Хоккеисты}}) is a 1965 [[Cinema of the Soviet Union|Soviet]] [[sports film|sports drama film]] written by [[Yury Trifonov]] and directed by [[Raphael Goldin]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=staff|title=Хоккеисты|url=http://ruskino.ru/mov/3655|language=Russian|publisher=ruskino.ru|accessdate=October 7, 2015}}</ref><ref name="Komsomolskaya Pravda 08-29-14">{{cite news|last1=НАЗАРЕНКО|first1=Елена|title=ФОТОГАЛЕРЕИ - Звезды|url=http://www.msk.kp.ru/photo/56378/1012238/|accessdate=October 7, 2014|language=Russian|publisher=[[Komsomolskaya Pravda]]|date=August 29, 2015}}</ref> It had English release in 1965 under the title '''''The Hockey Players''''', Finnish release as '''''Mestarit''''', and East German release as '''''Eishockeyspieler'''''.
== Plot == Thirty-year captain of the Rockets hockey team, Anatoly Duganov ([[Vyacheslav Shalevich]]), famous and experienced player decides to fight for the sport longevity of the ''old men'' as he tries to prove that it is still too early to retire. But in sports, including hockey, for a long time there is a certain stereotype: in 16 years is considered to be more junior player, at 18 years young player in the adult team, and in 25 years - is already a veteran. Acutely experiencing a quarrel with my girlfriend Maya ([[Elza Lezhdey]]), Duganov seeking participation in the decisive final match between the two strongest teams - and seek victory team.<ref name="cite 1">{{cite web|last1=staff|title=Хоккеисты|url=http://www.kino-teatr.ru/kino/movie/sov/7629/annot/|language=Russian|publisher=kino-teatr.ru|accessdate=October 7, 2015}}</ref>
==Cast== {{div col|colwidth=30em}} * [[Vyacheslav Shalevich]] as Anatoly Duganov<ref>[http://www.biograph.ru/index.php/whoiswho/7-theatre/1098-shalevichva Вячеслав Анатольевич Шалевич. Биография и фильмография]</ref> * [[Vladimir Ivashov]] as German Morozov * [[Aleksandr Kuznetsov (actor)|Aleksandr Kuznetsov]] as Sasha Morozov * [[Alexander Orlov (actor)|Aleksandr Orlov]] as Vladimir Vvedensky * [[Nikolai Rybnikov]] as Coach Lashkov * [[Gennadi Yukhtin]] as Peter Kudrichi * [[Georgiy Zhzhonov]] as Coach Sperantov * [[Mikhail Gluzsky]] as Chairman Ilyin * [[Lyusyena Ovchinnikova]] as Nadia Kudrichi * [[Lev Durov]] as Drunk Fan * [[Viktor Pavlov]] as Episode * [[Jakov Lenz]] as Grandpa at the Kiosk * [[Kir Bulychev]] as Young Sculptor * [[Elza Lezhdey]] as Maya * Yevgeny Shutov as Coach Christopher I. * Claudia Polovikova as Nina * Nikolai Grabbe as Nikolai Yershov * [[Nikolai Ozerov (sports person)|Nikolai Ozerov]] as Commentator * Yura Grishkin as Young Hockey Player * Alex Guryshev as Ivan Samsonov * Yulia Dioshi as Lashkov's Wife * German Kachin as Obsessive Fan * Viktor Kolpakov as Press Photographer * Vasily Neschiplenko as Team Doctor {{div col end}}
==Reception== Rated 7 out of 10 stars, the film is considered a decent representation of Soviet hockey, and interesting for fans of the sport.<ref>{{cite web|last1=staff|title=Вместе с фильмом "Хоккеисты" также смотрят|url=http://www.ivi.ru/watch/53518|language=Russian|publisher=ivi.ru|accessdate=October 7, 2015}}</ref>
